g.py does verify the spec-loading contract, but the required extension of test_schema_coverage.py to assert the diagnostic-vs-security-attestation distinction is entirely absent.","dimension":"completion","remediation":"Add a test to tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py that reads docs/output-schemas.md and asserts it contains the 'not a security attestation' (or equivalent 'diagnostic metadata') phrase for creation_channel_inferred.","reviewer_id":"completion-verifier","severity":"high"}],"material_fingerprint":null,"model":"anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6","remediation":"How to resolve the unmet criteria: for each one, decide whether the work is genuinely incomplete or simply undocumented. If a requirement is already satisfied but the proof is not discoverable from the code alone, add a comment to this ticket that documents the evidence — cite the concrete artifacts that meet the requirement (file paths and line ranges, commands and their output, links, or the reasoning that ties the work to the criterion). The completion verifier reads this ticket's comments, so evidence you record there is taken into account on the next verification. For any criterion whose work is genuinely unfinished, complete it, then re-verify.","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"completion_verifier_fail_v1","ticket_id":"e622-a596-3ceb-4f74","verdict":"FAIL"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMPLETION_VERDICT","timestamp":1784282686003107001,"uuid":"d074bf6a-a25d-42f4-84a2-76353c821296"}